## Context: Incremental Transitions

Organizational changes cannot happen in a big bang. Teams need to keep delivering while restructuring. A good transition plan:
- Breaks changes into phases that can each be completed without stopping delivery
- Orders phases so that each builds on the previous one
- Identifies risks at each phase and how to mitigate them
- Defines clear completion criteria for each phase
- Accounts for the temporary productivity dip during reorganization

Key principles:
- Move one service at a time, not all at once
- Change team boundaries before changing interaction modes
- Platform extraction should precede stream-aligned team restructuring
- Keep the value chain functional at every step

